TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {3946=Posted by Anonymous on 06/28/2010, 5856=Posted by Cristal on 01/11/2010, 8803=Posted by Shawn P on 10/15/2009, 4176=I've been to El Almacen many times, both for brunch and dinner. The food is consistently excellent, and sitting in the garden area on a breezy and cool day is a wonderful experience. I've never felt rushed to finish or leave, but I can say most of the servers are not overly attentive, but what's new in Brooklyn, from my experience anyways. I had my bday dinner there back in Feb on a crowded Sat night, with 12 guests, and for such a small place, they had our table ready to go right on time and it was a great time as a large group, sharing all the different tapas. Thankfully it's summer and the fabulous sparkling wine is back!
